                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <desc>The word God is not rubricated in the first three works</desc>
                        <desc>The final two works are not sufficiently visible to determine if the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                        <desc>There is no columetric layout of text</desc>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#8r #16r #24v #35v #43v #50v #60r" facs="008 016 025 036 044 051 060">folss. 8r, 16r, 24v, 35v, 43v, 50v, 60r, </locus>, etc. (line of alternating red and black dots);
                  <locus target="#88v #133r" facs="089 133">88v, 133r</locus> (multiple full stops between lines of red and black dots).
                  </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                          <locus target="#68r" facs="068">Fol. 68r</locus>
                           <desc>the midpoint of the Psalms is marked with the words “and this is its half.”</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>The end of this codex is badly damaged and many of the pages were not separated at the time of digitization to prevent further damage</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 32</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                          <locus target="#8" facs="008">Fol. 8</locus>
                           <desc>red string is sewn into the fore edge as navigation system</desc>
                           </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                          <locus target="#16 #24 #35 #43 #50 #73 #88 #103 #126" facs="016 024 035 043 050 073 088 103 126">Fols. 16, 24, 35, 43, 50, 73, 88, 103, 126</locus>
                          <desc>brown string is sewn into the fore edge as navigation system</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                          <locus target="#20v #27r #35r" facs="021 027 035">Fols. 20v, 27r, 35r</locus>
                           <desc>words of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                           </item>
                        <item xml:id="e7">
                          <locus target="#64r #66r #89r #110r #128r" facs="064 066 089 110 128">Fols. 64r, 66r, 89r, 110r, 128r</locus>
                          <desc>etc., text has been removed</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards of the traditional wood, front cover is missing.</decoNote>
